oracle.pg.hbase

Class OracleProperty<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.pg.hbase.OracleProperty<V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Property<V>

    public class OracleProperty<V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Property<V>
    This class implements the Property Tinkerpop3 interface for handling edge properties. A Property denotes a key/value pair associated with an Edge. A property is much like a Java8 Optional in that a property can be not present (i.e. empty). The key of a property is always a String and the value of a property is an arbitrary Java object. Each underlying graph engine will typically have constraints on what Java objects are allowed to be used as values.
